ABOUT PHILIPSPhilips is a diversified health and well-being company,
focused on improving people?s lives through meaningful innovations. As
a world leader in healthcare, lifestyle and lighting, Philips
integrates technologies and design into people-centric solutions,
based on fundamental customer insights. Headquartered in the
Netherlands, Philips employs over 122,000 employees in more than 100
countries with sales in 2011 surpassing EUR 22 billion.
YOUR
CHALLENGES / RESPONSIBILITIES
* Support Lead Generation in new and Grow Service sales in existing
markets
* Manage and drive campaigns in respective geographies to promote
Customer Services
* Gather local market and customer insights, and feed information
back to BIU/BG Marketing
* Understand BIU marketing customer segmentation and value
proposition, provide feedback on how to tailor to meet specific market
needs
* Identify sub-segments of customers in local market, and codify
their needs, and tailor existing value proposition (if needed)
* Support PCCI/IS Customer Services in the launch/introduction of new
Services and enhancements developed by the BG to the local market
* implement launch strategy for local market including any
localization of positioning, pricing and messaging to new and target
segments
* Support the training of the field sales force on the PH customer
services portfolio
* Elaborate Marketing strategies for value added services (VAS):
Philips Technology Upgrades (PTU), extended warranties, remote support
(not only tech remote service but application as well pro-active
monitoring)
* Lead CS Field marketing initiatives/activities like pricing
realizations, Contract Penetration, Growth, cost development, tubes, %
GM, bundling etc
WE ARE LOOKING FOR
* Bachelor?s degree in relevant field; MBA preferred
* 5 - 9 years in marketing, service or related field
* Experience in high tech, healthcare/med-tech solutions businesses
* Possess competitive and entrepreneurial mind-set to drive sales
growth in new and existing markets
* Possess collaborative mindset to work with cross-section of sales,
marketing, and analytics resources to develop solution-oriented sales
development programs
* Ability to think strategically and be flexible MBA preferred
* 5 - 9 years in marketing, service or related field
* Experience in high tech, healthcare/med-tech solutions businesses
* Possess competitive and entrepreneurial mind-set to drive sales
growth in new and existing markets
* Possess collaborative mindset to work with cross-section of sales,
